iSo what do I think? I think the man is a mixture of good ideas and		gopher.black	70
ibad. I think he's naturally brusque and his elevated position in		gopher.black	70
ihis narrow community has fed his ego dangerously, as any power is		gopher.black	70
iwont to do. 		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iI am also guilty of having been wrong in the past. I'm thankful		gopher.black	70
ithat most of my wrongness isn't in permanent written form and		gopher.black	70
iI don't have enemies who seek out my own poor behavior in the past		gopher.black	70
ito drag it into the light today. It's hard enough to change your		gopher.black	70
imind without being anchored to those past decisions through		gopher.black	70
iconstant reminder.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iStallman has lived his life in a tech world with tech solutions,		gopher.black	70
ilogic, and a type of pseudo-logical rhetoric that can make his		gopher.black	70
istatements seem detached or disingenuous. It's something I see		gopher.black	70
icommonly in communities dominated by autistic people, though it's		gopher.black	70
inot limited to those or necessarily present among all autistics.		gopher.black	70
iWhatever the case, it doesn't mesh well with the highly emotional		gopher.black	70
itopics such as sexual predation. The tone itself harms, which is		gopher.black	70
isomething I suspect Stallman is both unaware of and incapable of		gopher.black	70
iaddressing. Coming from a white man in position of power adds to		gopher.black	70
ithe harm and further alienates those who hear what he says. All		gopher.black	70
ithis harm comes separate from and in addition to the comments		gopher.black	70
ithemselves. He was rightfully argued against in that email list		gopher.black	70
iand I think the escalation of the issue into a public forum was		gopher.black	70
inecessary to balance the scales of power. Unfortunately in an		gopher.black	70
iinstitution like MIT and in a group like CSAIL the opinions of		gopher.black	70
iRichard Stallman are not in balance with the others speaking.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iWe do not currently have a mechanism in our society to address		gopher.black	70
ithese public social grievances of powerful people beyond seeking		gopher.black	70
ipunishment through their employment, platform, sponsorship, and		gopher.black	70
iother mechanisms that enable their power. Our public speech is		gopher.black	70
iunbalanced in power in favor of the rich and powerful, and so some		gopher.black	70
imeasures will necessarily be taken to counter it. 		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
